备位于右上角，Android 设备位于右下角），然后在搜索栏中输入号码。该号码将显示在“不在您的通讯录中”类别下。该人的电话号码和个人资料照片的右侧是单击“聊天”的选项，这使您可以直接与他们进行对话。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>到目前为止，唯一的例外包括通过网络链接开始对话或在群聊中回复未保存的号码。但是，这仍然需要您通过<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/whatsapp-feature-update-qr-code-contacts-152951474.html">二维码</a>或您已经认识的人的邀请进入聊天。 WhatsApp 的最新更新正在向所有用户推出，因此您应该很快就能使用新功能。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/whatsapp-makes-it-easier-to-send-messages-to-unsaved-numbers-093511724.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/whatsapp-makes-it-easier-to-send-messages-to-unsaved-numbers-093511724.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 701e490e-3ac4-47b9-8095-70c8864a8f4a</guid><dc:creator>萨拉·菲尔丁</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 20 Jul 2023 09:35:11 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689847704</ingested><modified> 2023-07-20T10:08:26+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Sarah Fielding]]></category><media:content height="534" medium="image" url="https://media.zenfs.com/en/reuters.com/03c084f4fcef33110f6d89320da04a26" width="800"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="534" medium="image" url="https://media.zenfs.com/en/reuters.com/03c084f4fcef33110f6d89320da04a26" width="800"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Meta introduces broadcast tool Channels on WhatsApp]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Kevin Mitnick, formerly the world’s ‘most-wanted’ hacker, has passed away]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>凯文·米特尼克（Kevin Mitnick）曾是世界上最受通缉的计算机黑客之一，于 7 月 16 日<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2023/07/20/technology/kevin-mitnick-dead-hacker.html">去世</a>，享年 59 岁。根据他的<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.dignitymemorial.com/obituaries/las-vegas-nv/kevin-mitnick-11371668">讣告</a>，米特尼克与胰腺癌抗争了一年多，目前正在匹兹堡大学医学中心接受治疗。他的讣告写道：“他一生的大部分内容读起来就像一个小说故事。”这也许是描述他的故事的完美方式。米特尼克第一次渗透计算机系统早在 1979 年，但直到 1988 年他才因复制公司软件而被定罪并被判处 12 个月监禁。</p><p>他在被监管释放期间侵入了 Pacific Bell 的语音邮件计算机，然后在 90 年代作为逃犯继续侵入手机网络以及公司和政府网站。米特尼克还参与盗窃了数千份文件和信用卡号码，但他的讣告称他“从未从任何‘受害者’那里拿过一毛钱。”他最终于 1995 年被捕，并被指控非法使用电话接入设备和计算机欺诈。显然，当局认为他当时可以获得价值数百万美元的公司商业机密。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>米特尼克在监狱里度过了五年，他被释放时将其描述为“假期”。从那时起，他改变了自己的职业生涯，选择成为一名白帽黑客和网络安全顾问。 2011 年，他成为 KnowBe4 的股东兼首席黑客官，该公司为客户提供安全意识培训和模拟网络钓鱼平台。在这一切发生之前，米特尼克在 12 岁时就想出了如何利用洛杉矶的公共交通系统，通过记住公交车时刻表和打孔卡，然后获得自己的打孔工具系统，这样他就可以整天乘坐公交车。米特尼克身后留下了他的妻子金伯利·米特尼克和他们未出生的孩子。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/kevin-mitnick-forming-the-worlds-most-wanted-hacker-has-passed-away-084912966.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/kevin-mitnick-formerly-the-worlds-most-wanted-hacker-has-passed-away-084912966.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 6e7457ea-db3b-4dfc-a​​c2c-5a77e45e4a49</guid><dc:creator>玛丽埃拉·穆恩</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 20 Jul 2023 08:49:12 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689853649</ingested><modified> 2023-07-20T11:47:32+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Information Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Society & Culture]]></category><category><![CDATA[Crime & Justice]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mariella Moon]]></category><media:content height="2667" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/116f9da0-26f3-11ee-aff7-724b3b2cc231" width="4000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2667" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/116f9da0-26f3-11ee-aff7-724b3b2cc231" width="4000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[John Leyba/The Denver Post via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[DENVER, CO - MARCH 13: Kevin Mitnick was in Denver to give a presentation to BBVA Compass bank clients on March 13, 2018 at the Halcyon Hotel in Denver Colorado.  Kevin Mitnick made headlines in 1995 when he was arrested by the FBI for hacking computers. He really put a face on this new cybersecurity threat even though what he was caught doing at the time seems not very nefarious (hacking voice mail systems, snooping around corporate networks). He's apparently changed his ways and runs his own company. Clients hire him to break into their own computer networks to see how secure they really are.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[931646430 - Kevin Mitnick - hacker / cybersecurity]]></media:title></media:content></item></channel></rss>